o curb fraud and litigation by ensuring all property commitments are formally documented, unlike current practices of using plain paper or notarized agreements with weaker legal standing.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/haryana-to-mandate-registration-of-property-sale-agreements-for-enhanced-transparency/129128111?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-33350/129128111.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}